Macon.Ingleside Historic District:
The Ingleside Historic District is a planned neighborhood and a historic district in Macon, Georgia which was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2016.
About 549 acres (2.22 km2) in area, in 2016 it included 641 contributing buildings, four contributing structures, and two contributing sites, as well as 115 non-contributing buildings.
Architects W. Elliott Dunwody, Jackson Holliday, Ellamae Ellis League, Harry A. MacEwen, William F. Oliphant, Neel Reid, and Bernard A. Webb each designed one or more works in the district.
